2. In this question we examine the Singleton design pattern.
(a) Why might you decide to lazy-initialise a singleton instance rather than
initialise it in its field declaration? Provide code examples of both approaches
to illustrate your answer.

A possible reason for using lazy-initialisation would be if object creation is
expensive and it is desirable to delay it, or if it may not be required at all.

(1) SingletonEager uses a Scala object, which automatically creates a singleton

(2) SingletonLazy